==Guided Mode==
[[File:Guided Mode.webp|thumb|220x220px|A screencap of the "Guided Mode" menu.]]
'''Guided Mode''' was a [[Special:MyLanguage/Menus|menu]] and UI feature intended for users who were new to VRChat, however any user could enable and use the Guided Mode menu. It was announced in the April 28, 2023<ref>[https://ask.vrchat.com/t/developer-update-28-april-2023/17808 '28 April 2023 - Developer Update'] on ''ask.vrchat.com''; retrieved September 1, 2025.</ref> [[Developer Update]], then initially released on May 3, 2023 in the VRChat 2023.2.2<ref>[https://docs.vrchat.com/docs/vrchat-202322 VRChat 2023.2.2] on ''docs.vrchat.com''; retrieved December 4, 2024.</ref> update. The Guided Menu heavily simplified world and avatar exploration and tweaking for settings. It was revealed on the [https://youtu.be/MyrEvss-Dzw&t=77 VRChat 2023.2.2 Video Patchnotes], and was present in the VRChat client for a few months before being silently removed.

The following patchnotes<ref>[https://docs.vrchat.com/docs/vrchat-202322 VRChat 2023.2.2] on ''docs.vrchat.com''; retrieved February 15, 2025.</ref> were introduced alongside the released the release of Guided Mode:

<blockquote>''Introducing '''Guided Mode'''!''

*''Guided mode is a simplified Quick Menu meant for new users, making it easy to explore VRChat and learn about vital functions.''
*''This mode is available to all users in the Open Beta for testing.''
*''You can exit Guided Mode to return to the normal Quick Menu.''
*''Once this release goes to Live, Guided Mode will only be accessible to some new users for further testing''
*''Later on, we will release it fully and optionally allow all users to enable the feature if you prefer it''</blockquote>

==Old age verification badges ==

[[File:Age-Verification-Badges.webp|thumb|A screencap of the old 'age verification' badges.]]
When [[Age Verification|age verification]] was in early access, and early stages of public release, there were two badges available for those who went through the age verification process. 
*Age Verified
* Verified 18+

It should also be noted that these badges are not the same as achievable [[Badges|profile badges]]. The Age Verified Badge was removed, and the Verified 18+ badge was changed from red to blue, stating: <blockquote>''"Essentially, this marker simply meant that you had completed the process - you had verified your identity, but you may not have been 18 or older."''</blockquote>and <blockquote>''"Red looked really bad on some headsets and didn't match our visual design."''
<ref>[https://discord.com/channels/189511567539306508/503009489486872583/1338982044251721778 Message from strasz] on VRChat [[Discord servers|Discord]]; retrieved February 12, 2025.</ref></blockquote>

==18 Hour clock==
The '''18 Hour clock''' mode was a setting originally introduced with the [[Quick Menu#Clock|clock]]'s release on April 1st, 2024. The feature was eventually removed during the 2025.3.1 beta cycle, build 1678, cited with the [https://feedback.vrchat.com/open-beta/p/1678-18-hour-clock-mode-is-missing following reason on the VRChat Feedback board]:
<blockquote>
''This change was intentional. As our localization stack matures, the time for the 18 hour clock had come...''</blockquote>

The 18 hour clock divides the day into two phases: AA and PA. From midnight (00:00) to 6:00 PM (18:59), the time follows the standard 24-hour clock format and is labelled with the "AA" suffix. At 18:59 AA, the clock resets and switches to 1:00 PA, marking the start of the second phase of the day. The PA phase runs from 1:00 PA to 6:00 PA. After 6:00 PA, the clock resets back to 00:00 AA, starting the next day. 

